      "id": "jshell-201-hashmap-md",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "## HashMap — Key/Value Lookups\n\nA `HashMap<K, V>` stores **key → value** pairs and gives you O(1) average-case lookup, insert, and delete. It does **not** guarantee insertion order (use `LinkedHashMap` for that, or `TreeMap` for sorted keys).\n\nThink of it like a dictionary: you look up a word (key) to find its definition (value).",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "anchor": null,
      "dependsOn": [],
      "pipelineSteps": []
    },
    {
      "id": "jshell-201-hashmap",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "//@ anchor: hash-map-basics\n//@ description: HashMap basics\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n// --- HashMap basics ---\nHashMap<String, Integer> stockPrices = new HashMap<>();\n\n// put(key, value) — adds or overwrites\nstockPrices.put(\"AAPL\", 178);\nstockPrices.put(\"GOOG\", 141);\nstockPrices.put(\"MSFT\", 415);\nstockPrices.put(\"AMZN\", 185);\nstockPrices.put(\"NVDA\", 878);\n\nSystem.out.println(\"MSFT price    : \" + stockPrices.get(\"MSFT\"));\nSystem.out.println(\"Has TSLA?     : \" + stockPrices.containsKey(\"TSLA\"));\nSystem.out.println(\"Map size      : \" + stockPrices.size());\n\n// getOrDefault — avoids NullPointerException for missing keys\nint tslaPrice = stockPrices.getOrDefault(\"TSLA\", -1);\nSystem.out.println(\"TSLA (or -1)  : \" + tslaPrice);\n\n// Iterating over entries\nSystem.out.println(\"\\n--- All stock prices ---\");\nfor (Map.Entry<String, Integer> entry : stockPrices.entrySet()) {\n    System.out.printf(\"  %-6s $%d%n\", entry.getKey(), entry.getValue());\n}\n\n// Practical pattern: update a counter\nstockPrices.merge(\"AAPL\", 5, Integer::sum);  // AAPL += 5\nSystem.out.println(\"\\nAAPL after +5 : \" + stockPrices.get(\"AAPL\"));",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "anchor": "hash-map-basics",
